INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES('39', '1', '2014-05-26 11:15:21', '2014-05-26 11:15:21', '<h3><strong>How to apply:</strong></h3>\r\nTo apply for the undergraduate program applicants have to apply through a <strong>pre-paid “Teletalk”</strong> mobile phone.\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>At 1<sup>st</sup> go to the message option of your “Teletalk” mobile phone.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Then type <strong>NSTU</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Give a space and type <strong>the first three digits of the name of the educational board of HSC</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>?</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Give space and type <strong>HSC roll number</strong>, give space and type <strong>passing year of HSC</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Give space and type <strong>the first three digits of the name of the educational board of SSC</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Give space and type <strong>SSC roll number</strong>, give space and type <strong>passing year of SSC</strong> and</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">At last give another space and type <strong>B </strong>(as group B contains ‘pharmacy’ in NSTU admission test system).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Send the message to <strong>16222</strong>.</p>\r\nExample:\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>NSTU&lt;space&gt;COM&lt;space&gt;123456&lt;space&gt;2014&lt;space&gt;COM&lt;space&gt;123456&lt;space&gt;2012&lt;space&gt;B</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This example is for Comilla Board. Here applicants have to put their own HSC &amp; SSC roll numbers in place of 123456.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For different boards the codes are Comilla (COM), Sylhet (SYL), Barisal (BAR), Chittagong (CHI), Dhaka (DHA), Dinajpur (DIN), Jessore (JES), Rajshahi (RAJ) and Madrasa (MAD).</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If all the above information is correct then the applicant will receive a SMS containing his/her name, desired group, admission fee &amp; a pin number and the applicant will be asked to confirm these. To confirm the information the applicant will have to SMS again to 16222. For confirmation please type:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>NSTU&lt;space&gt;YES&lt;space&gt;PIN Number&lt;space&gt;Any Contact Mobile no</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong> </strong>Then send the message to <strong>16222</strong>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> <strong>N.B: </strong>The application fee will be charged only when the applicant send the confirmation SMS, otherwise no application fee will be charged.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"3\">\r\n	<li>If there is sufficient balance in the mobile account of the applicant then the application fee will be charged and the applicant will receive a confirmation SMS regarding the admission roll no.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"4\">\r\n	<li>The application procedure is same as above for O/A level students. In this case applicants have to write GCE in place of education board</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Example:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>NSTU&lt;space&gt;GCE&lt;space&gt;123456&lt;space&gt;2012&lt;space&gt;A</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Here applicants have to put their own candidate number of A level examination in place of 123456.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"5\">\r\n	<li><strong>Regarding the admission in QUOTA (5% of total seats):</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Applicants wish to apply in the following QUOTA has to apply according to aforementioned procedure.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Freedom Fighter Quota (FFQ), Tribal Quota (TQ)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Example:</p>\r\n<strong>NSTU&lt;space&gt;COM&lt;space&gt;123456&lt;space&gt;2014&lt;space&gt;COM&lt;space&gt;123456&lt;space&gt;2012&lt;space&gt;B</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>&lt;space&gt;FFQ</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Admission Requirements:</strong></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Students those who have passed their SSC/Equivalent examination in 2011/2012 and HSC/Equivalent examination in 2013/2014 from Science division and from Secondary &amp; Higher Secondary / Madrasha education board can apply for the admission examination. To qualify for the admission examination an applicant must have GPA 3.5 in SSC/Equivalent examination and GPA 3.0 with additional/optional subject in HSC/Equivalent examination and a total GPA of 6.5. If any student has a GPA below than C in any subject in HSC/Equivalent examination his/her application will not be considered.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Students of ‘O’ level must pass a total of 5 subjects with Physics, Mathematics, Chemistry and Biology and must pass any of the two subjects from Physics, Mathematics, Chemistry and Biology in their ‘A’ level examination. If any student has a GPA below than C in any subject of ‘A’ level examination his/her application will not be considered.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"2\">\r\n	<li>Those who have passed SSC / Equivalent examination / ‘A’ level examination before 2011 cannot apply for the admission examination.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"3\">\r\n	<li>An applicant must have Mathematics in his/her HSC examination.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">International students can apply directly; but they will be considered for admission after the analysis and approval of the provided certificates by the University Equivalence Committee.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Application fee:</strong></h3>\r\nThe application fee for the admission examination is degree course is 500 BDT.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.nstupharma.org/study-programs/undergraduates/admission/nstu-admission-2013-14/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-445\">NSTU admission circular for session 2013-14</a></strong></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Admission', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'admission', '', '', '2014-07-12 14:54:32', '2014-07-12 14:54:32', '', '37', 'http://www.nstupharma.org/?page_id=39', '0', 'page', '', '0');
